  "prompt": "What are some good books about time management?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended books on time management:\n\n1. \"Getting Things Done\" by David Allen\n- Offers a comprehensive productivity system\n- Focuses on organizing tasks and reducing mental clutter\n\n2. \"The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People\" by Stephen Covey\n- Provides principles for personal and professional effectiveness\n- Includes strategies for prioritizing and time management\n\n3. \"Deep Work\" by Cal Newport\n- Emphasizes focused, distraction-free work\n- Discusses strategies for improving concentration and productivity\n\n4. \"Eat That Frog!\" by Brian Tracy\n- Provides practical tips for overcoming procrastination\n- Teaches how to prioritize and tackle important tasks\n\n5. \"The One Thing\" by Gary Keller and Jay Papasan\n- Focuses on identifying and concentrating on the most important task\n- Helps eliminate unnecessary activities\n\n6. \"Time Management for Professionals\" by Dale Carnegie\n- Classic time management advice\n- Offers practical strategies for improving efficiency\n\n7. \"Essentialism: The Disciplined Pursuit of Less\" by Greg McKeown\n- Emphasizes doing fewer things, but doing them better\n- Helps eliminate non-essential tasks\n\nThese books offer various approaches to managing time more effectively.",
